<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="539" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d539">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/1009.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Blanchard</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-31">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 31, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>President Zamor, wife and child, sailed last night. Charles Zamor and
                            ministers remain in French Legation. Terrific firing last night.
                            Absolute calm in the city to-day. <hi rend="italic">Hancock</hi> arrived
                            this morning. Conferred with commander, and under the circumstances no
                            occasion for landing troops. The city is under martial law commanded by
                            General Redmond Polynice, Acting Commandant of Arrondissement, who is
                            the sole authority for order.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Blanchard</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>